opicID=1595.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   That was one of the major ones</span><hr size=1> IIRC, it was 'Q' from the EQ-monks board.  He was a major figure in the EQ monk comunity; he ran one of the two monk boards in existence at that time (the other being The Dojo).  He sent e-mail to every monk that ever posted on his board about how to do it. The details are a lot different than you hinted at, Ermok -- you're mixing up two different dupe bugs.  Here's the opening paragraph from the monk that was banned:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> On July 28th I have found a reproducible duping bug and reported it to  Erollisi Marrs GM Valtron. After inquiring about a reward for reporting the bug I was told that they have no policy to reward people for reporting bugs.  I have tried numerous times to speak with Valtrons supervisor or anyone superior to him and failed. After explaining to Valtron the seriousness of the bug and that if it were to get publicized it would hurt the economy greatly he accused me of threatening to publicize a bug/exploit and banned me. While I have not threatened to do such a thing, now that I am banned that seems like a good idea, so here goes<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->BTW, you're also mixing up how-to details of two different dupe bugs, Ermok.  Also, there were three more rather public ones that I recall, too.  VI's little assertion that there has only been one such bug is ridiculous, though they might be talking about only one known outstanding unfixed dupe bug and not one in all the history of EQ.<br>
<br>
